            "answer_text": "Industrial pollution is any pollution that can be traced directly to industrial activity, such as this discharge.  This type of (typically point source) pollution is a big problem in countries where industrial practices are booming and growing at a large pace. This is because environmental agencies are overrun. They simply don't have time to manage byproducts, emission and waste because of the growing industry. ",
